[{"id":34735,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msub><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msub><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mn>3</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math>&nbsp;is a linear differential equation.</p><p>Here&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>General solution will be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p>Given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>So, the equation of the curve is&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now putting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>3</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34860,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["$y \\sqrt{\\tan x}=x+c$","$y \\sqrt{\\cot x}=\\tan x+c$","$y \\sqrt{\\tan x}=\\cot x+c$","$y \\sqrt{\\cot x}=x+c$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Given, $\\sin 2 x\\left(\\frac{d y}{d x}-\\sqrt{\\tan x}\\right)-y=0$ or, $\\frac{d y}{d x}=\\frac{y}{\\sin 2 x}+\\sqrt{\\tan x}$ or, $\\frac{d y}{d x}-y \\operatorname{cosec} 2 x=\\sqrt{\\tan x}$\nNow, integrating factor (I.F) $=e^{\\int-\\operatorname{cosec} 2 x}$ or, I.F $=e^{-\\frac{1}{2} \\log |\\tan x|}=e^{\\log (\\sqrt{\\tan x})^{-1}}$ $=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{\\tan x}}=\\sqrt{\\cot x}$\nNow, general solution of eq. (1) is written as\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text { y (I. F.) }=\\int \\mathrm{Q}(\\text { I.F.) } d x+c \\\\\n&\\therefore y \\sqrt{\\cot x}=\\int \\sqrt{\\tan x} \\cdot \\sqrt{\\cot x} d x+c \\\\\n&\\therefore y \\sqrt{\\cot x}=\\int 1 . d x+c\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dXdl7fCMq5T1A8wnNuKIHujN-I3iGV7MzmHzzcN4FY8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (12 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":34639,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["$e^e$","$e^{e^2}$","$e^{2e}$","$e^{2e}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given differential equation is $\\dfrac{dy}{y} = (2 + \\log_e x) dx$<br><br>Integrating both sides, we get:<br><br>$\\int \\dfrac{dy}{y} = \\int (2 + \\log_e x) dx$<br><br>$\\log_e y = 2x + x \\log_e x - x + C$<br><br>$\\log_e y = x + x \\log_e x + C$<br><br>Since the curve passes through $(1, e)$, substitute $x = 1$ and $y = e$:<br><br>$\\log_e e = 1 + 1 \\cdot \\log_e 1 + C$<br><br>$1 = 1 + 0 + C \\Rightarrow C = 0$<br><br>The equation of the curve is $\\log_e y = x + x \\log_e x$<br><br>To find $f(e)$, substitute $x = e$:<br><br>$\\log_e y = e + e \\log_e e$<br><br>$\\log_e y = e + e(1) = 2e$<br><br>$y = e^{2e}$<br><br>Answer: $e^{2e}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34779,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Given:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>cot</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cot</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>This is a linear differential equation of the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>&#160;I.F&#160;</mtext><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cot</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sec</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Solution is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sec</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p>Now,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Then the function is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Put&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34695,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>85</mn><mo>°</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mi>F</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>95</mn><mo>°</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mi>F</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mi>F</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>80</mn><mo>°</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mi>F</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Given: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>160</mn><mi>T</mi></munderover><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></munderover><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msubsup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi>log</mi><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>160</mn><mi>T</mi></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>log</mi><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>−</mo><mi>log</mi><mn>80</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>log</mi><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mn>80</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Now, using the value <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mn>15</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>120</mn><mo>°</mo></msup></math> we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>120</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>K</mi><mo>·</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>80</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∴</mo><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mn>45</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>45</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mn>45</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mn>45</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mn>45</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mi>F</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34721,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>e</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>This is a linear differential&nbsp;equation.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>Then solution of&nbsp;differential&nbsp;equation is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>sec</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></math></p><p>Given:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>At <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>sec</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>e</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34833,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"The given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>.</mo></math> can be written as<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mi>i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;which is a liner differential equation of the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8201;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#8201;</mo><mi>Q</mi></math>&nbsp;are the function of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;or constants.</p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>Integrating factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>And, the solution of the linear differential equation is,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>I</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>I</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&#8901;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>sec</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#8901;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&#8901;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo></math> hence</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Thus, the curve is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now, put <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>36</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34780,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfenced></math></p><p>Integrate</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p>given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn></math></p><p>at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>45</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34843,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>64</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>13</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>49</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Given differential equation can be written as<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> , which is a linear differential equation.<br /><br />If <math><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br />Solution is<br /><br /><math><mi>y</mi><mo>.</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>.</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>.</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math><br /><br />Since, given curve passes through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />Hence,&nbsp;<math><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>.<br /><br />So,&nbsp;<math><mi>y</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>49</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34845,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["a circle of radius two","a circle of radius one","a hyperbola","an ellipse"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\left(x^2-y^2\\right) d x+2 x y d y=0$\n$$\n\\Rightarrow \\frac{d y}{d x}=\\frac{y^2-x^2}{2 x y}\n$$\nLet $y=v x$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{d y}{d x}=v+x \\frac{d v}{d x} \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & v+x \\frac{d v}{d x}=\\frac{v^2 x^2-x^2}{2 v x^2} \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & v+x \\frac{d v}{d x}=\\frac{v^2-1}{2 v} \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & x \\frac{d v}{d x}=\\frac{-v^2-1}{2 v} \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & \\frac{2 v d v}{v^2+1}=-\\frac{d x}{x}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nAfter integrating, we get\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\ln \\left|v^2+1\\right|=-\\ln |x|+\\ln c \\\\\n&\\frac{y^2}{x^2}+1=\\frac{c}{x}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nAs curve passes through the point $(1,1)$, so $1+1=c \\Rightarrow c=2$\n$x^2+y^2-2 x=0$, which is a circle of radius one.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":34652,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["$\\frac{1-e^2}{e^4}$","$\\frac{2 e-1}{e^3}$","$\\frac{e-1}{e^4}$","$\\frac{1-e^3}{e^4}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}<br/>& f(x)=x-1 \\\\\n& f(f(x))=f(x)-1=x-1-1=x-2 \\\\\n& g(f(f(x)))=e^{x-2} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\frac{d y}{d x}=e^{-2 \\sqrt{x}} \\times e^{x-2}-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x}} y \\\\\n& \\frac{d y}{d x}+\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x}} y=e^{x-2 \\sqrt{x}-2} \\text { which is L.D.E } \\\\\n& \\text { I.F. }=e^{\\int \\frac{d y}{\\sqrt{x}}}=e^{2 \\sqrt{x}}<br/>\\end{aligned}$<br/>Its solution is<br/>$\\begin{aligned}<br/>& y \\times e^{2 \\sqrt{x}}=\\int e^{2 \\sqrt{x}} \\times e^{x-2 \\sqrt{x}-2} d x+c \\\\\n& y \\times e^{2 \\sqrt{x}}=\\int e^{x-2} d x+c \\\\\n& y \\times e^{2 \\sqrt{x}}=e^{x-2}+c<br/>\\end{aligned}$<br/>$\\text { Given } \\mathrm{x}=0, \\mathrm{y}=0 \\Rightarrow 0=\\mathrm{e}^{-2}+\\mathrm{c} \\quad ; \\mathrm{c}=-\\mathrm{e}^{-2}$<br/>$\\therefore \\mathrm{y} \\times \\mathrm{e}^{2 \\sqrt{\\mathrm{x}}}=\\mathrm{e}^{\\mathrm{x}-2}-\\mathrm{e}^{-2}$<br/>$\\text { when } \\mathrm{x}=1, \\mathrm{y} \\times \\mathrm{e}^2=\\mathrm{e}^{-1}-\\mathrm{e}^{-2}$<br/>$y=\\frac{e^{-1}-e^{-2}}{e^2}=\\frac{\\frac{1}{e}-\\frac{1}{e^2}}{e^2}=\\frac{e^2-e}{e^5}=\\frac{e-1}{e^4}$<br/>Option (1) is correct","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (8 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34838,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Differential Equations","question":"","options":["$\\quad \\log _{e}\\left|\\frac{2-x}{2-y}\\right|=x-y$","$-\\log _{e}\\left|\\frac{1-x+y}{1+x-y}\\right|=2(x-1)$","$-\\log _{e}\\left|\\frac{1+x-y}{1-x+y}\\right|=x+y-2$","$\\log _{\\mathrm{e}}\\left|\\frac{2-y}{2-x}\\right|=2(y-1)$"],"answer":1,"solution":"The given differential equation\r\n\r\n$\\frac{d y}{d x}=(x-y)^{2}$\r\n\r\nLet $x-y=t \\Rightarrow 1-\\frac{d y}{d x}=\\frac{d t}{d x}$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow \\frac{d y}{d x}=1-\\frac{d t}{d x}$\r\n\r\nNow, from equation (1)\r\n\r\n$\\left(1-\\frac{d t}{d x}\\right)=(t)^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow \\quad 1-t^{2}=\\frac{d t}{d x} \\Rightarrow \\int d x=\\int \\frac{d t}{1-t^{2}}$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow-x=\\frac{1}{2 \\times 1} \\ln \\left|\\frac{t-1}{t+1}\\right|+c$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow-x=\\frac{1}{2} \\ln \\left|\\frac{x-y-1}{x-y+1}\\right|+c$\r\n\r\n$\\because$ The given condition $y(1)=1$\r\n\r\n$-1=\\frac{1}{2} \\ln \\left|\\frac{1-1-1}{1-1+1}\\right|+c \\Rightarrow c=-1$\r\n\r\nHence, $2(x-1)=-\\ln \\left|\\frac{1-x+y}{1-y+x}\\right|$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null}]